title: Mapping Cylinder
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

For a {{map}} between {{topsps}} $$f : X \to Y$$, the ''mapping cylinder'' $$M_f$$ is the [[Quotient Space|Quotient Topology]] of the [[Disjoint Union]] $$(X \times I) \amalg Y$$ obtained by identifying each $$(x,1) \in X \times I$$ with each $$f(x) \in Y$$.

